================================================================================
JavaScript / TypeScript dependencies (frontend)
================================================================================

The frontend single-page application depends on the following npm packages
in the production bundle:

  @fontsource/inter          OFL-1.1   (font — see above)
  @types/sql.js              MIT
  @zxcvbn-ts/core            MIT
  @zxcvbn-ts/language-en     MIT
  client-zip                 MIT
  exifr                      MIT
  jsqr                       Apache-2.0
  phosphor-svelte            MIT
  qrcode                     MIT
  sql.js                     MIT       (includes an embedded SQLite build,
                                        which is in the public domain)
  svelte                     MIT

All Apache-2.0 attribution notices and MIT copyright lines are preserved in
each package's installed directory under `frontend/node_modules/`. The
complete per-package attribution is generated at release time into
`frontend/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.txt` (via `npx license-checker --production`)
and shipped inside the signed release tarball.

Build-time and test-only dependencies (Vite, TypeScript, ESLint, Playwright,
Vitest, svelte-preprocess, etc.) are not redistributed in the production
bundle and their licenses are not reproduced here.


